methods.void clear(): Removes all of the mappings from this map (optional operation).
methods.Object clone(): Returns a shallow copy of this AbstractMap instance: the keys and values themselves are not cloned.
methods.boolean containsKey(Object key): Returns true if this map contains a mapping for the specified key.
methods.boolean containsValue(Object value): Returns true if this map maps one or more keys to the specified value.
methods.Set entrySet(): Returns a Set view of the mappings contained in this map.
methods.boolean equals(Object o): Compares the specified object with this map for equality.
methods.V get(Object key): Returns the value to which the specified key is mapped, or null if this map contains no mapping for the key.
methods.int hashCode(): Returns the hash code value for this map.
methods.boolean isEmpty(): Returns true if this map contains no key-value mappings.
methods.Set keySet(): Returns a Set view of the keys contained in this map.
methods.V put(K key, V value): Associates the specified value with the specified key in this map (optional operation).
methods.void putAll(Map m): Copies all of the mappings from the specified map to this map (optional operation).
methods.V remove(Object key): Removes the mapping for a key from this map if it is present (optional operation).
methods.int size(): Returns the number of key-value mappings in this map.
methods.String toString(): Returns a string representation of this map.
methods.Collection values(): Returns a Collection view of the values contained in this map.
